                "Research reactor at ZFK, Rossendorf."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The flux ratio of thermal to fission neutrons,F(t)/F(S)",
                "was determined using 27Al(n,a)24Na and 24Mg(n,p)24Na",
                " (for fiss.neutrons) and Na-23(n,g)Na-24(for thermal)",
                " and their cadmium ratios.",
                "Reaction       Effect.n-energy  X-section  Cd-ratio",
                "Mg-24(n,p)Na-24    7.2 MeV       1.53mb       1.",
                "Al-27(n,a)Na-24    8.8 MeV       0.725mb      1.",
                " Ref. A.Fabry, rep.BLG-465 (1972).",
                " Compiler's note =",
                " For limit of 'MONIT' number, those values are not",
                " included in data section.-"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "50-100 mg NH(4)-Cl or KCl, and with 10-15 Mg (NH(4))*",
                "2-HPO(4) as phosphor standard sample,in quartz ampoule."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "MOMIX"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " (n,g) reaction leading to the same daughter product",
                "was used for comparison.(Cl-35(n,a)P-32, P-31(n,g)P-32)",
                "Only relative measurement of the activities of the",
                "sample and standard is to be performed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 18 cm3 Ge(Li) detector with a 4096 channel pulse",
                "height analyzer (Nuclear Chicago).",
                ".Bell-shape counter VA-Z-320 and radiation detectors",
                "VA-V-100, VA-G-120 and VA-G-24A,( VEB Messelektronik,",
                "Dresden),  for beta counting."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The cross-section of Cl-35(n,a)p-32 for fission-",
                "neutron, sig(S) is deduced from the following equation,",
                " sig(S)=sig(t)*(F(t)/F(S))*(1/p)*(r/(r-1))*(1/r'),",
                "where",
                " sig(t)- (n,g) cross-section for 'thermal' neutrons,",
                " F(t)/F(S)- flux ratio of thermal to fission neutrons,",
                " p- isotopic disturbing coef. Which can be determined",
                "  to measure the relative activity of target and",
                "  standard,",
                " r- cadmium ratio of (n,g) reaction,",
                " r'- cadmium ratio of threshold reaction.",
                " Cadmium ratios of P-31(n,g)P-32 and Cl-35(n,a)P-32",
                "were determined to be 60 and 1 respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DG",
                "B-"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " 2.75 MeV gamma peak of Na-24 and P-32 beta activity."
              ]
            }
          ],
